<div id="review_449288515" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/449288515" />
    <a title="Jimagn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14291907-jimagn"><img alt="Jimagn" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/449288515?book_show_action=true">Nov 05, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jimagn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jimagn" href="/user/show/14291907-jimagn">Jimagn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer449288515" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5390344445787685501">This is a very clearly written and well-researched book on religion and belief in god. I&apos;ve often wondered how religion came to have such a secure place in most people&apos;s lives and whether religion is a cultural construct that humanity may one day discard. After reading this book it is clear how religion evolved with humanity. The prognostication for the path of continued evolution is not so clear. As we have profoundly changed our environment, we may find this trait has lost its survival value. </span>
  <span id="freeText5390344445787685501" style="display:none">This is a very clearly written and well-researched book on religion and belief in god. I've often wondered how religion came to have such a secure place in most people's lives and whether religion is a cultural construct that humanity may one day discard. After reading this book it is clear how religion evolved with humanity. The prognostication for the path of continued evolution is not so clear. As we have profoundly changed our environment, we may find this trait has lost its survival value. Hopefully our species will be able to adapt.<br /><br />Also of note is his treatment of contingency and necessity in the process of evolution. Well worth your time to read. Highly recommended.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5390344445787685501" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


