<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer10258509980198637902">Michael Brant Shermer (born September 8, 1954 in Glendale, California) is an American science writer, historian of science, founder of The Skeptics Society, and Editor in Chief of its magazine <i>Skeptic</i>, which is largely devoted to investigating and debunking pseudoscientific and supernatural claims. The Skeptics Society currently has over 55,000 members.<br/><br/>Shermer is also the producer and co-host of t</span>
  <span id="freeText10258509980198637902" style="display:none">Michael Brant Shermer (born September 8, 1954 in Glendale, California) is an American science writer, historian of science, founder of The Skeptics Society, and Editor in Chief of its magazine <i>Skeptic</i>, which is largely devoted to investigating and debunking pseudoscientific and supernatural claims. The Skeptics Society currently has over 55,000 members.<br /><br />Shermer is also the producer and co-host of the 13-hour Fox Family television series Exploring the Unknown. Since April 2004, he has been a monthly columnist for Scientific American magazine with his Skeptic column. Once a fundamentalist Christian, Shermer now describes himself as an agnostic nontheist and an advocate for humanist philosophy.<br /><br /><br />more info: <br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://us.macmillan.com/author/michaelshermer">http://us.macmillan.com/author/michae...</a><br /><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Shermer">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_...</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="10258509980198637902" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
